724436f-c.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 64th Street (West)
724436f-c.text:
(1)
West End Ave., west side, south from West 65th to 64th Streets.
The view shows buildings being demolished for expansion of the N.Y.C.R.R.
yards.
March 19, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, from a different angle. Also shown is the West 64th
Street side of building being demolished.
March 19, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
The same, in the opposite direction (eastward), from inside of the
N.Y.C.R.R. yards. Building in the center, is the one being denolished
on view No. 2 aspecially.
March 19, 1930.
P. L Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

724433f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 64th Street (West)
724433f-a.text:
West End Ave., south from West 64th Street, showing on the west side
of same the yards of the New York Central Railroad and a power plant of
the Consolidated Edison Company.
December 19, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

724434f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 64th Street (West)
724434f-a.text:
West End Ave., east side, north from and including West 64th Street,
as viewed from a point slightly southward of same. The gas holder of
the Consolidated Edison Company is in the 65th to 66th Streets block.
November 25, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
